correction_response: This tweet is misleading. According to the Florida Department of Health, the highest single-day death toll was 276 on August 11, 2021. The number mentioned seems to be a cumulative total over several days, not a single day count. Always refer to official health department data for accurate information.
note_1_text: Per WPLG-TV (CBS Miami): "Those deaths did not all happen over the past day and span back weeks." https://www.local10.com/news/florida/2021/09/09/florida-adds-another-1296-covid-19-deaths-12k-more-cases/
